# Widget View Binding

Inside a widget scope, the view is registered as itself and all interfaces it implements. This allows child scopes to resolve the view by any of its interfaces (e.g. `ICameraProvider`).

## Pattern

- `WidgetScopeInstaller` registers the view with `AsSelf().As<IWidgetView>()` and `As(iface)` for each additional interface
- Views that provide cross-cutting concerns (camera, etc.) implement dedicated interfaces
- Child widgets resolve by interface: `ICameraProvider` instead of concrete `ViewLayerView`
